# crontab.example — application-pipeline Pi cron entry
#
# Install with: crontab -e
# Replace <user> with the actual Pi user (e.g. pi, agent).
# The runbook in docs/pi-setup.md documents the full substitution procedure.
#
# flock -n ensures the single-writer invariant (ADR-0010): if a previous
# invocation is still running, the new tick exits immediately without
# launching a second pipeline instance.
#
# The pipeline fires once per calendar day. The exact local time is your
# choice; the entry below fires at 07:00 UTC. Adjust the hour to suit your
# timezone and preferred delivery window.

0 7 * * * /usr/bin/flock -n /var/lock/application-pipeline.lock /home/<user>/application-pipeline/current/scripts/pi-tick.sh >> /home/<user>/application-pipeline/data/logs/cron.log 2>&1
